BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup Metrotrails": "https://www.meetup.com/metrotrails/events/314094515/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_metrotrails
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Metrotrails Hiking
UID:event_314094515@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260412T031143Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260412T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260412T180000
SUMMARY:Chester County Pastoral Hike
DESCRIPTION:Metrotrails: NJ\, PA\, NY Metropolitan Area Hiking and More!\n
 Join us for this excellent rural hike in Chester County PA\, which ties to
 gether a different way the recent Chester County hikes we've been doing.\n
 From the start\, we will do the easier back roads.\nThe only lined road we
  will be on is the very beginning.\nWe will walk through the historic Shee
 der-Hall Covered Bridge\, then out to the main road for under a half mile\
 , We then turn onto some back roads including Sheeder Mill Road\, HIlltop 
 Road\, Birchrun Road\, Green Lane\, and Bartlett Road.\nAt least half of t
 his is unpaved\, and none of these named roads even have lines in them\, m
 aking them narrow\, lightly used\, and very pleasant.\nWe'll soon get on t
 he Horse-Shoe Trail from where we left off. This takes us through pleasant
  woods\, and then out into cultivated farm fields.\nBits of the Horse-Shoe
  Trail also follow these little used roads.\nWe'll continue on the HST to 
 Art School Lane\, then make our way east and pass the historic Vincent Bap
 tist Church and cemetery.\nWe'll continue to the intersection with Miller 
 Road\, where we'll begin following the Bryn Coed Trail System.\nThis amazi
 ng and long trail system weaves though woods and fields keeping with the o
 verall theme of the hike.\nAmazing pastoral views will make for a relaxing
  walk that will lead us almost all the way back to our stating point.\nWe'
 ll get on one more dirt road before the end\, and then an abandoned road t
 hat is now in the trail system right back to where we parked.\nDistance 15
  mi\nIf needed\, contact me at 908 343 8374
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/metrotrails/events/314094515/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260402T200609Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260402T200609Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup Somocon": "https://www.meetup.com/somocon/events/313547810/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_somocon
X-SOURCE:Meetup: South Mountain Conservancy
UID:event_313547810@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260412T031144Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260412T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260412T120000
SUMMARY:SMC Trail Work Volunteer Day- CHANGED DATE
DESCRIPTION:South Mountain Conservancy Activities Meetup Group\n**TRAIL WO
 RK** will begin this year with finishing work on the Lenape Trail reroute 
 below the Beech Brook Cascades. The steps are in (see photo)\, but final t
 read improvements on switchbacks and throughout are needed. We will meet a
 t the Dog Park (11 Bear Lane) and head down to the Lenape trail from there
 .\n\nTrail work is physically challenging but very satisfying as we use ha
 nd tools to build and repair trails. Participants must be 15+ years. Those
  younger than 18 must be accompanied by an adult. Participants should wear
  long pants due to [ticks](https://www.somocon.org/?page_id=193928&fb) and
  sturdy shoes\, and bring gloves (though backup gloves will be available).
  Tools\, water\, and a snack will be provided. (Registration is not requir
 ed though if you sign up on Meetup\, it helps us know how many tools to br
 ing.)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/somocon/events/313547810/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260226T232715Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260226T232715Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
