 career_fairs/37dfb726-9582-4e23-9c82-6561adbc3e11/student_preview\n \nDes
 cription:\nCalling all community and service-minded students exploring cl
 inical and non-clinical career options!\n \nAre you looking for a job or 
 internship? Are you curious about the career paths you can pursue with yo
 ur major or graduate program? If so\, the Community and Social Services C
 areer Expo is an amazing opportunity to meet employers that align with yo
 ur professional interests. Whether you are a freshman or a graduate stude
 nt\, this event is designed to help you explore career possibilities\, ga
 in networking experience by talking with employers\, and make connections
  that may eventually lead to a job or internship. There will be fun mixed
  in with the opportunity to win raffle prizes! \n \nMore Information:- Ma
 rk your calendar! Monday\, April 13\, 3:30pm - 6:30pm\, University Hall C
 onference Center (7th Floor)- Visit with non-profit\, government\, and co
 rporate employers that have a service-oriented mission- Discover opportun
 ities with campus organizations and departments\, including international
  experiences that incorporate social impact- Pre-registration is strongly
  encouraged - Register on Handshake!- Event details and employer list can
  be found on Handshake. - Dress neatly and bring resumes! Check out Rocky
 's Closet for free professional attire. \n \nThis event is ideal for grad
 uate and undergraduate students seeking jobs and internships in: Counseli
 ng\, Child Advocacy\, Justice Studies\, Social Work\, Political Science\,
  Psychology and so much more!\n \nCo-sponsored by: College of Humanities 
 and Social Sciences\, College for Community Health\, Office of Community 
 Engagement and Partnerships\, Office of Experiential Education and Career
  Connections\, Office of Government Relations\, Office of International A
 cademic Initiatives\n \nQuestions? Contact Jennifer Dudeck-Lenis at dudec
 klenisj@montclair.edu.\n \n\nHosted by: College of Humanities and Social 
 Sciences (CHSS)\, College for Community Health\, Government Relations and
  Community Affairs \, Office of International Academic Initiatives\, Offi
 ce of Community Engagement and Partnerships\, The Office for Experiential
  Education and Career Connections\n\nAdditional Information can be found 
 at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12352317
