SUMMARY:5K Training - No Boundaries - Orientation Night
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class.\n\nClick here to register 
 for the early bird price\, available until April 3rd.\n\nClick here for 
 registrations April 3rd and later.\n\nHave you always wanted to run or walk 
 a 5K but didn't know how to begin training? Maybe you are nervous or don't 
 want to do it alone? Maybe you have had a hard time sticking to a training 
 program in the past? If you answered "Yes" to any of the above\, our iconic 
 beginner program is perfect for you. Often the first step is the 
 hardest.\n\nThe camaraderie of a group and experience of your coaches and 
 mentors provide great support toward healthier habits and lifestyle. This 
 program is designed for people just starting a walking/running routine for 
 the first time\, restarting after a winter hiatus and those who want to run 
 faster or longer. In 8 weeks\, meeting twice a week\, our fun\, 
 unintimidating program will help you walk\, walk-run or run across the 
 finish line at the Fitzgerald 5k Lager Run in June.\n\nIn collaboration 
 with Dawn and John Fabbro of Fleet Feet Montclair
LOCATION:Montclair - Anderson Park\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School
UID:LibCal-10306-15993855
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/15993855
END:VEVENT
