SUMMARY:Protecting Your Financial Future: FINRA Investor Advocacy Program
DESCRIPTION:\n\n\n\n\n\nWant to protect your financial future? This 
 presentation is designed to help individuals guard against financial fraud 
 and to make informed decisions before entrusting your money with financial 
 professionals. Participants will leave with a basic understanding of how to 
 spot red flags\, an overview of investor rights\, and insight into what the 
 Financial Industry Regulatory Authority ("FINRA") is and how it can help 
 investors when problems arise. \n\nAndrew Marino is a 2026 J.D. Candidate 
 at Seton Hall University School of Law and a Student Advocate for the FINRA 
 Investor Advocacy Program (“IAP”). He is a life-long resident of New 
 Jersey and graduated from Denison University. Mr. Marino has worked as a 
 judicial intern for the District Court of New Jersey\, as well as a Summer 
 Associate for a New Jersey firm. Mr. Marino also serves as a Senior Editor 
 for the Seton Hall Law Review. \n\n This free\, 45-minute presentation is 
 for educational purposes and does not sell or recommend any financial 
 services. The FINRA IAP is one of 10 securities arbitration clinics 
 throughout the United States. The FINRA IAP program at Seton Hall is a pro 
 bono program\, which provides free legal representation to New Jersey 
 residents of modest means with securities fraud claims. The IAP was 
 established by a grant from FINRA.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Classroom
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult Services, Finances
UID:LibCal-10306-16635866
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16635866
END:VEVENT
