DESCRIPTION:Jazz Career Panel\nGUESTS\nLydia LiebmanSeth AbramsonKaren Ken
 nedy\n1-2 pm - Roundtable Discussion2-2:30 pm - Q & A\nLydia LiebmanLydia
  Liebman is an award-winning jazz media strategist and founder of Lydia L
 iebman Promotions\, one of the most active and respected PR firms in jazz
 . Since launching the company from her Emerson College dorm room\, she ha
 s led more than 800 release campaigns\, worked with major jazz artists an
 d institutions\, and served on the faculty of both the Roc Nation School 
 of Music and The New School.\nSeth AbramsonSeth Abramson is a Grammy Awar
 d–winning producer\, guitarist\, and entrepreneur. As President of Rabbit
  Moon Productions\, Director of Jazz for The Gilmore\, and Senior Artisti
 c Advisor for The Jazz Legacies Fellowship\, he helps artists build caree
 rs\, develop major projects\, and navigate the business of music at the h
 ighest level.\nKaren KennedyKaren Kennedy is the founder of 24 Seven Arti
 st Development\, a full-service management and consulting company that ha
 s supported the careers of Grammy-nominated and award-winning artists for
  more than three decades. A respected arts leader\, educator\, and advoca
 te\, she has held influential roles across the music industry\, higher ed
 ucation\, and national arts organizations\, with a longstanding focus on 
 artist development\, access\, and inclusion.\n\nHosted by: The College of
  the Arts\n\nAdditional Information can be found at: https://montclair.ca
 mpuslabs.com/engage/event/12412700
DTEND:20260416T183000Z
DTSTAMP:20260412T030706Z
DTSTART:20260416T170000Z
