SUMMARY:[MILL Senior Friday] AARP: Spotting Scams & Staying Safe
DESCRIPTION:Join us on Fridays for a day full of events for Seniors with 
 the MILL @ MPL! All events are free and open to the public. Registration is 
 recommended unless otherwise noted.\n\n\nHave you ever been approached with 
 a fraudulent offer or been a victim of identity theft? These days\, 
 scammers are sophisticated. And separating the real from the phony can be 
 tough--especially when emotions are running high. Join us for a free event 
 where we'll take a look into the latest scams\, how to avoid them and what 
 to do if you've been targeted. \n\nWe'll explore:\n\n\n	Common scams\, and 
 how to spot and avoid them\n	Tactics scammers use to target 
 individuals\n	What to do if you're asked for personal 
 information\n	Resources to help protect yourself and your family\n\n\nHOW 
 TO REGISTER\nThis class is run by AARP. Please register directly through 
 their website here.\n\nFor questions about MILL classes please call 
 973-744-3278.\n\nMILL @ MPL is made possible through a partnership between 
 the MILL\, Montclair Public Library and Partners for Health.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Auditorium
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult Services, Computers & Technology
UID:LibCal-10306-16669698
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16669698
END:VEVENT
