SUMMARY:Where Do We Go From Here: Chaos or Community? Film event and discu
 ssion 7:30 at FCC
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260418T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260418T210000
DTSTAMP:20260412T031140Z
UID:587vj7q9jebfec59emogivj493@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20260418T193000
SEQUENCE:0
CREATED:20260403T152436Z
DESCRIPTION:<h4><span>Join us in a conversation for our time. </span><sp
 an><span><span>Foremost Productions</span></span><span> will present <
 span>“A Community Cultural Event Honoring the Legacy of Dr. Martin Luthe
 r King Jr. and Dr. Maya Angelou”</span> at the <span>First Congregat
 ional Church of Montclair</span></span>. </span></h4><p><span>The evening
  will feature a screening of the award-winning documentary film “Maya 
 Angelou – Reflections of a Blessed Soul\,” followed by a special tal
 kback discussion to include the film’s director Hafiz Farid and exec
 utive producer Shelley Grodner Seidenstein.</span></p><p><span>Inspired by
  Dr. King’s timeless question\, <b><span>“Where Do We Go From Here
 : Chaos or Community?”</span></b>\, the evening invites audiences to ex
 plore the relevance of the words and wisdom of both Dr.King and Dr. Ange
 lou in today’s world. </span></p><p><span>The event is free and open 
 to the public\, made possible through the support of community sponsors wh
 o believe in the importance of accessible cultural programming.</span></p>
 <p><i><span>“We can learn to see each other and see ourselves in each ot
 her and recognize that human beings are more alike than we are unalike.”
  -Maya Angelou</span></i></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260403T152521Z
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
X-SOURCE:First Congregational Church Montclair
END:VEVENT
