DESCRIPTION:**2nd Annual Mitzvah Day**  \n  \nGather as a community in ser
 vice to perform mitzvot for our local social action partners\, Israel\, an
 d Shomrei itself. All ages welcome! There is a Mitzvah for everyone\, incl
 uding kids! Babysitting available for 1st grade and under. Breakfast nosh 
 provided.  \n  \nOpen to Shomrei Community &amp\; Your Friends.  \n  \n**P
 articipate in any or all activities:**   \n  \nDONATE SUPPLIES** Donate it
 ems needed to make our Mitzvot a reality. Visit our online wish list to ma
 ke a purchase. Make sure items are delivered to Shomrei **by April 15th.**
  Drop-offs at Shomrei are welcome. Or\, fund the supplies with a monetary 
 donation. You don't have to donate items to participate (but it helps!)  \
 n**online wish list: https://shomrei.org/wishlist**  \n**alternative monet
 ary donation:** **https://shomrei.org/supplies**  \n **VOLUNTEER YOUR TIME
  on April 19:**  \n- Assemble Senior grocery bags for Toni's Kitchen\n- So
 rt donated spring &amp\; summer clothes for Human Needs Food Pantry\n- Ass
 emble "Welcome to Your New Home" kits for Family Promise\n- Make sandwiche
 s for MESH\n- Garden outdoors at Shomrei\n- Make friendship bracelets for 
 a school in Israel (kid-specific)\n- Color pictures/write letters for seni
 ors (kid-specific)\n- Write thank you cards for pet adoptions for the Mont
 clair Animal Shelter (kid-specific)\n\n  \n**register here: https://shomre
 i.org/mitzvah  \n  \n**PARTICIPATE IN A DRIVE**  \nBring breakfast cereals
  and/or adult and children’s summer clothing for Human Needs Food Pantry
  to Shomrei (Drop off at Shomrei or bring with you on Mitzvah day.)  \n  \
 nKey fob required for building entry.  \n   \n**Questions?**  \nContact th
 e Office  \noffice@shomrei.org  \n(973) 746-5031\n\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20260408T165620Z
TRANSP:OPAQUE
URL;VALUE=URI:https://teamup.com/kstx8swyw669kakgqa/events/1892966145
X-SOURCE:Congregation Shomrei Emunah
END:VEVENT
