SUMMARY:Practical Spanish 1
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to 
 register.\n\nThis class is for those of you who know little to no Spanish 
 and are interested in acquiring some practical communication skills. You 
 will be introduced to basic greetings and practice useful questions and 
 answers. You will learn the fundamentals of Spanish pronunciation while 
 mastering introductory grammar and vocabulary.\n \nTopics 
 covered:\n\n\n	conversation/questions\n	greetings\n	personal 
 information\n	expressions of courtesy\n	feelings\n	asking for 
 direction\n	talk about needs and wants\n	where people are 
 from\n	Alphabet\n	Numbers/days/date\n	Colors\n	Basic commands\n	Some 
 ar/er/ir  regular verbs\n	Verb to be: ser/estar\n	Verb to go: ir\n	Verbs: 
 tener/necesitar/querer\n	Ir   a\n	Negation\n	Subject pronouns/difference 
 between tú/usted\n	Gender and number of nouns/definite/indefinite 
 articles\n	Some adjectives including cuánto/a\n	The expression 
 “Hay”\n	Basic geography\, culture and food\n\n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Classroom\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Language
UID:LibCal-10306-16395749
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16395749
END:VEVENT
