DTSTART:20260421T221500Z
DTEND:20260421T234500Z
DTSTAMP:20260421T000000Z
SUMMARY:Savory and Sweet Arab Cuisine: Fattoush Salad and Jallab NEW
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to 
 register.\n\n\n\nIn another edition of FARAH’s Sweet & Savory Flavors of 
 Arab Cuisine series at MPL\, discover the aromatic spices of Arab cuisine. 
 Join Lilianne Gooch for a guided cooking demonstration on how to make two 
 classic dishes with an emphasis on spices: one sweet and one savory. \n 
 \n\n\n\nFattoush: The Vibrant Taste of the Levant\n\nThe perfect chopped 
 salad\, Fattoush is a refreshing\, crunchy\, and colorful staple in Arab 
 cuisine featuring watercress or romaine lettuce\, tomatoes\, cucumber\, 
 radishes\, and fresh herbs\, all tossed in a tangy signature 
 lemon-sumac-pomegranate molasses vinaigrette. Added crunch and flavor comes 
 from crispy toasted pita chips topped with za’atar. Join us to learn 
 about the unique spices that make up this flavorful Arab salad.  \n 
 \n\n\n\nJallab: The Essence of Arab Hospitality\n\nTransport your senses to 
 the Levant with this traditional and refreshing drink. Learn how to mix 
 date\, grape and carob molasses with rose water into a fragrant 
 non-alcoholic drink. Perfect for warm days\, it is traditionally served 
 chilled and topped with pine nuts and raisins. This is the quintessential 
 Arab mocktail.  \n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Auditorium\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Culinary
UID:LibCal-10306-16356819
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16356819
END:VEVENT
