SUMMARY:Weekly Labyrinth Walks\, Wednesdays 11am-1pm
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260422T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260422T130000
DTSTAMP:20260412T031140Z
UID:ludgoqjjiam6rn46dm98mt3a9e@google.com__20260422
SEQUENCE:1
CREATED:20240529T134031Z
DESCRIPTION:<u></u><span>Weekly: Wednesdays 11am-1pm in the Sanctuary</spa
 n><span> </span><span></span><i> </i><p></p><p><span>Take your soul for a 
 walk on the labyrinth.  We are pleased to offer labyrinth walks each Wedn
 esday in the mid-day as a chance to connect with your soul in our beautifu
 l sanctuary. <br><br>The labyrinth is an ancient spiritual tool \, a mode
  of “walking prayer” that invites us to go deeper in our walk with God
 .  Our labyrinth\, modeled on one in Chartes Cathedral in France\, sits a
 s the center of our Sanctuary\, a constant metaphor for our spiritual live
 s.  Just like the labyrinth\, our lives are not linear\, but filled with 
 twists and turns.  Sometimes we make great progress\, and other times we 
 feel we are going backwards.  But if we trust in the path we will find ou
 rselves in the center -- the heart of God.</span> <br></p><p><span>All are
  welcome to take their souls out for a healing walk... no experience neces
 sary! </span> <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://baristanet.co
 m/2014/03/labyrinth-walk-meditation-satisfies-soul/&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=
 calendar&amp\;usd=2&amp\;usg=AOvVaw0Y_UBYHduSYmZAtn0VUHmP" target="_blank"
 ><span>Check out this lovely write up on Baristanet</span></a> <span>from 
 the Spring 2014.</span> <br></p><p><a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=h
 ttps://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue%3D2%26v%3DD453ajtWb74%26feature
 %3Demb_logo&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;usd=2&amp\;usg=AOvVaw0jnAO
 _0I_l5nW8Ob7EnbtQ" target="_blank"><span>Watch this video</span></a> <span
 >to find out more about walking the labyrinth. If you’ve never done so c
 ome out one Wednesday evening and give it a try. It is a wonderful way to 
 nourish your soul and spend some quiet time in prayer or meditation.</span
 ></p><u></u>
LAST-MODIFIED:20251215T182737Z
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
X-SOURCE:First Congregational Church Montclair
END:VEVENT
