SUMMARY:Wine Confidence 101: Understanding the Basics
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to 
 register.\n\nThis introductory course offers a comprehensive overview of 
 essential wine concepts\, designed to establish or strengthen your 
 foundational knowledge and support your ongoing appreciation of wine. 
 \n\nOver the 5-week course\, we will review the primary grape varieties and 
 styles of dry white\, rosé\, red\, and sparkling wines\, as well as 
 explore viticulture fundamentals and the winemaking process. We will 
 explore the major wine-producing countries and differences among grape 
 varieties and wine styles. We will review how to taste and critically 
 evaluate wine from visual assessment through aftertaste. For historical 
 context\, the course provides an overview of wine’s origins\, its 
 evolution\, and the business aspects of winemaking. A solid foundation also 
 includes guidance on appropriate tools for opening wine bottles\, optimal 
 storage\, and serving temperatures to enhance your overall wine experience. 
 \n\nBy the end of the 5-week class\, you will have gained a deeper 
 understanding of the many aspects of dry and sparkling wines so you are 
 thoroughly conversant about wine and have tasted between 20 – 25 
 different wines from around the world! \n\nTHIS EVENT IS 21  Students will 
 be required to show a government ID to the instructor upon arriving at the 
 first session.\n\n \n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Conference Room\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Culinary
UID:LibCal-10306-16255562
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16255562
END:VEVENT
