URL:https://www.meetup.com/cloud-data-driven/
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Cloud Data Driven
UID:event_313895997@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260412T031142Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260423T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260423T133000
SUMMARY:Agentic AI Finance: Governed Metrics\, Open Access\, Automated Act
 ion on Databrick
DESCRIPTION:Cloud Data Driven\nLarge finance organizations already rely on
  dashboards and reports\, but the real challenge is enabling automation wi
 thout breaking governance or auditability. This session shares how a globa
 l finance organization implemented agent-driven workflows on the Databrick
 s Data Intelligence Platform using Unity Catalog\, metrics views\, and ope
 n lakehouse patterns.\n\nThe talk walks through a real implementation wher
 e finance metrics are defined once using metrics views\, protected with at
 tribute-based access control and automated classification\, and reused con
 sistently across reporting\, analytics\, and automation. Power BI connects
  directly to governed lakehouse tables and metrics for enterprise reportin
 g\, while Iceberg-compliant clients consume Delta tables through Uniform\,
  enabling open access without duplicating data.\n\nAgentic workflows obser
 ve certified metrics and events\, assist with variance investigation\, ano
 maly triage\, and operational follow-ups\, and propose actions that remain
  traceable and reviewable. Early results indicated several hours of manual
  investigation effort saved per reporting cycle and faster anomaly triage\
 , without introducing additional governance or audit risk. The session inc
 ludes an architecture walkthrough and demo using synthetic data\, reflecti
 ng real finance constraints\, trade-offs\, and lessons learned when moving
  from reporting to governed\, open\, and action-oriented analytics.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/cloud-data-driven/events/313895997/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260322T150331Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260322T150331Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Montclairfoundation Calendar Of Events": "https://montclairfoundation.org/event/botanicals-watercolor/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:montclairfoundation_calendar_of_events
X-SOURCE:Montclair Foundation
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260423T133000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260423T143000
DTSTAMP:20260411T231147
CREATED:20260331T143945Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260331T224515Z
UID:10007528-1776951000-1776954600@montclairfoundation.org
SUMMARY:MILL Botanicals Watercolor Workshop
DESCRIPTION:These classes are a Partner Program with the Montclair Institute for Lifelong Learning. To register please visit: http://schedulesplus.com/montclair/kiosk \nThursdays\, 1:30 PM – 2:30 PM \nApril 23 – Spring Botanicals Watercolor Workshop – Instructor: Karen DeLuca: Learn the art of painting flowers and leaves in watercolors. Bring your own paints/brushes to class but we will have some to loan. \nMay 21 – What’s in Bloom Tour – Join Laura Roberts\, Director of Horticulture at Van Vleck\, for a journey through the beauty of the season. Discover enchanting details and appreciate majestic specimens. Outdoor tour\, so please dress for the weather with appropriate footwear. (Outdoor Program\, indoors if inclement weather) \nMay 28 – Focus on Flowers Walk – Spend an afternoon in the garden taking a close-up look at the beauty of flowers. After learning about each flower\, discover helpful hints in capturing photos using your phone or camera. Instructors: Laura Roberts and Tracey Diamond (Outdoor Program\, indoors if inclement weather) \nJune 4 – Birds of Prey Program – Flat Rock Brook Nature Center will visit Van Vleck with live birds of prey. Learn fascinating facts about these incredible creatures that live right here in New Jersey. (Indoor Program) \nJune 11 – Late Spring Blooming Tree tour – This guided tree identification walk led by Laura Roberts will focus on spring-blooming trees. This is an outdoor tour\, so please dress for the weather with appropriate footwear. (Outdoor Program\, indoors if inclement weather) \nJune 18 – Birds and Art – We’ll learn about some of our favorite resident birds at Van Vleck with Naturalist Jenny Aley and discuss their summer activities. We will also explore our creative side with a simple painting or sketching activity that will help us identify some of our beautiful native birds. No experience necessary – all levels of birders and artists welcome! (Indoor Program) \nJune 25th – Mindfulness in the Garden – Jodi Brooks will guide us through very gentle stretching & breathwork\, and an outdoor contemplative garden walk. This is a practice of slowing down\, cultivating quiet and paying attention to our senses. All levels are welcome. No experience needed. Cold or rainy weather – class will be held indoors\, with a short walk outdoors (weather permitting). (Outdoor Program\, indoors if inclement weather)
URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/event/botanicals-watercolor/
LOCATION:Van Vleck House & Gardens\, 21 Van Vleck Street\, Montclair\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Classes,Adults
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://montclairfoundation.org/content/uploads/2025/07/20230919_140412-scaled.jpg
END:VEVENT
