SUMMARY:The Sonnet: Talk and Writing Workshop NEW
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to register.\n\nA 
 two-part lecture/discussion and hands on workshop. We will explore the 
 surprising multicultural Sicilian roots of the sonnet form\, in the Palermo 
 court of Frederick II Holy Roman Emperor ("wonder of the world"). Then (in 
 honor also of Shakespeare's birthday!) we will write our own sonnets\, with 
 step by step support for those who would like it!\n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Tower Room\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Lectures / History & Culture, Writing
