SUMMARY:African Dance for Beginners NEW
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to 
 register.\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n			Join us for our all-new African Dance 
 Workshop\, an exciting opportunity to move\, connect\, and celebrate 
 culture through rhythm and community. Led by Karen Miles of Zawadi African 
 Dance and accompanied by two live drummers\, this energizing class welcomes 
 dancers of all levels.\n			\n		\n	\n\n\nThe workshop begins with a 
 10-minute guided warm-up to prepare the body with rhythmic movement and 
 grounding techniques. Participants will then learn Dansa\, a vibrant 
 traditional dance of the Malinké people from Upper Guinea.\n\nDansa is 
 traditionally performed as a joyful celebration during community 
 gatherings\, often encouraging collective labor while strengthening unity 
 and fostering a powerful spirit of togetherness. Experience the rich 
 cultural traditions\, dynamic rhythms\, and uplifting communal energy that 
 make West African dance so inspiring.\n\nNote: This class takes place at 
 DiRasa Gallery\, 4 Lackawanna Plaza in Montclair.\n
LOCATION:Montclair - Offsite\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Dance
UID:LibCal-10306-16406927
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16406927
END:VEVENT
