DTSTART:20260423T223000Z
DTEND:20260424T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260423T000000Z
SUMMARY:Open Book\, Open Mind\; Michael Luo\, "Strangers in the Land"
DESCRIPTION:New Yorker writer and executive editor Michael Luo will talk to 
 Matthew Purdy\, editor at large of The New York Times\, about about his 
 landmark study\, "Strangers in the Land: Exclusion\, Belonging\, and the 
 Epic Story of the Chinese in America." Co-presented by AAPI New 
 Jersey.\n\n“You can’t paint a complete picture of America without [the 
 story of Chinese Americans]\, and the New Yorker journalist Michael Luo 
 tells it persuasively in 'Strangers in the Land'... [The book] succeeds 
 through its little biographies of individuals – a range of quirky and 
 fascinating figures\, both Chinese and white\, who drive the narrative. . . 
 [and offer] a view on the full complexity of American immigration.” 
 —The New York Times Book Review\n\n\n\nDoors open at 6 p.m. The 
 discussion will be followed by an audience Q&A and book sales and signing 
 with Watchung Booksellers. \n\nOpen Book / Open Mind is sponsored by 
 Montclair Public Library Foundation\, Watchung Booksellers\, Anonymous\, 
 David and Mary Lee Jones\, and our individual Underwriters. We are also 
 grateful for the generous support of our in-kind sponsors\, First 
 Congregational Church of Montclair\, The George\, and Amanti Vino. To 
 support Open Book / Open Mind and other library programs\, click here to 
 donate.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Auditorium\, Montclair Main - Conference Room\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Open Book / Open Mind
UID:LibCal-10306-15725988
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/15725988
END:VEVENT
