SUMMARY:Advanced Woodworking
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to 
 register.\n\nFor those with previous woodworking experience\, this class 
 will allow students to learn more advanced techniques. Students will have 
 the opportunity to start a new project or bring in a project from home that 
 they would like to work on.\n\nThis course will cover:\n- Advanced use of 
 saws\, drills\, routers\, kreg jigs\, dowel jigs\, biscuit jointers\, table 
 saw\, router table\n- Various types of joinery\, fasteners\, and 
 finishing\n- Different edge finishes on router table\n- Carving tools\n- 
 Corner clamps\, bar clamps\n\nPREREQUISITE: Completion of Woodworking 
 101\n\nMaterials fee is dependent on project and payable to instructor at 
 the beginning of class.\nSmall Shelves / Spice Rack / Record Storage Box: 
 $20-$25\nShelves / End Tables / Night Stands / Stools: $60-75\nCoffee 
 Table: $100\n
LOCATION:Montclair - Montclair High School\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Arts & Crafts
UID:LibCal-10306-16502621
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16502621
