DTSTART:20260424T173000Z
DTEND:20260424T193000Z
DTSTAMP:20260424T000000Z
SUMMARY:[MILL Senior Friday] World of Film with Mark Phelan
DESCRIPTION:Join us on Fridays for a day full of events for Seniors with 
 the MILL @ MPL! All events are free and open to the public. Registration is 
 recommended unless otherwise noted.\n\n\nSmall Lives in Big Cities film 
 series\; Paterson (2016)— Paterson\, NJ.\n\nABOUT THE INSTRUCTOR\nMARK 
 PHELAN - I am a lifelong film fanatic who eats\, breathes\, sleeps and 
 drinks movies. I have studied with Donald Spoto at the New School in NYC 
 and have a BA and MA in Speech and Theatre from MSU. I have also worked as 
 an actor and have directed several plays in local regional and community 
 theaters\, including the Whole Theatre in Montclair and the Paper Mill 
 Playhouse in Millburn\, NJ. I am currently working as an adjunct professor 
 teaching\, among other courses\, Introduction to Cinema.\n\nHOW TO 
 REGISTER\nThis class is run by the MILL. Please register for classes 
 directly through their website here.\n\nFor questions about MILL classes 
 please call 973-744-3278.\n\nMILL @ MPL is made possible through a 
 partnership between the MILL\, Montclair Public Library and Partners for 
 Health.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Auditorium
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult Services, Books, Film & Theater
UID:LibCal-10306-16669790
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16669790
END:VEVENT
