SUMMARY:Friends of MPL Volunteer Information Session
DESCRIPTION:Friends of the Library is a group of volunteers who provide 
 support for the library. Volunteer opportunities include a range of 
 activities\, from shelving books to assisting at library events. People can 
 find something that fits the amount of time they can commit. Come to this 
 information and Q&A session to learn more about the variety of ways you can 
 help out!\n\nWhether or not you can attend\, feel free to reach out to Adam 
 Grace at friends@montclairlibrary.org if you are interested in joining the 
 Friends.
