SUMMARY:Golf: Outdoor
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to 
 register.\n\nGolf is a sport for a lifetime. Learn the fundamentals: 
 backswing\, downswing and follow-through. Acquire the feel of the swing and 
 develop dexterity through drills and exercises. Discussion will touch on 
 rules\, etiquette\, safety\, golf lingo\, equipment and history of the 
 game.\n\nLocation: Sessions will be held at Millburn Municipal Golf 
 Course\, 335 White Oak Ridge Road\, Short Hills.\n\nNote: If you have golf 
 clubs\, bring them to class. Clubs will be provided for those without them. 
 Proper golf attire required\; no t-shirts\, baseball hats\, spandex pants\, 
 short shorts\, jeans\, sweatpants or tank tops. Instructor usually contacts 
 students by phone so please let the Adult School know if that arrangement 
 is an issue. Instructor usually contacts students prior to the start of 
 class by phone so please let the Adult School know if that arrangement is 
 an issue.\n
LOCATION:Montclair - Offsite\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Fitness, Games
UID:LibCal-10306-16418074
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16418074
