SUMMARY:The Courage To Care: Inspiring a New Generation
DESCRIPTION:Children’s literature has always explored the importance of 
 kindness\, helping and standing up for others and moral courage. Please 
 join us as Montclair authors\, Dan Gill and Janice Cohn read from their 
 respective books\, No More Chairs and Freedom Pancakes for Ukraine. Both 
 books explore moral courage in ways that resonate with children today. A 
 book list curated by students attending Montclair’s public and private 
 middle schools and high schools will be available as a takeaway.
