SUMMARY:Mah Jongg - Tournament-Style Play NEW
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to 
 register.\n\nLearn how to master the speed and strategy of Mah Jongg for 
 tournaments.\n\nAfter years of playing in casual Mah Jongg games\, more 
 experienced players may be looking to challenge themselves in tournament 
 play but feel intimidated by the idea.  Are you good enough?  What is a 
 "table" rule versus a NMJL rule? The trick to tournament play isn't just 
 skill\, but is the confidence in that skill and your knowledge of NMJL 
 rules. This class will clarify those rules and give tips to make you 
 confident in your play.\n\nNote: Students must bring their own 2026 
 National Mah Jongg League hand card to class. The Bellevue Avenue Branch is 
 NOT wheelchair accessible.\n
LOCATION:Montclair Bellevue Ave Branch - Kids Place\, Montclair Bellevue Avenue Branch
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Bellevue Avenue Branch, Games
UID:LibCal-10306-16498850
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16498850
END:VEVENT
