DTSTART:20260427T221500Z
DTEND:20260427T234500Z
DTSTAMP:20260427T000000Z
SUMMARY:(POSTPONED) LIVING GREEN: Change Your Diet\, Help the Planet NEW
DESCRIPTION:This is a free Adult School class. Click below to 
 register.\n\nThe food we eat-- how it is produced\, processed\, and 
 shipped--has a huge environmental impact\, and is a significant driver of 
 climate change. Project Drawdown\, a leading nonprofit research hub that 
 identifies\, reviews\, and promotes the most effective\, science-based 
 solutions to reverse global warming\, found that decreasing our consumption 
 of animal products is one of the most important things that people can do 
 to help slow climate change and improve the natural environment on our 
 planet. Come to this session to learn more about how our food system 
 affects the environment\, and how can you start moving towards a 
 greener--and healthier--diet.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Auditorium\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Lectures / History & Culture
UID:LibCal-10306-16410701
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16410701
END:VEVENT
