X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_wordpress_montclair_meetup
URL:https://www.meetup.com/wordpress-montclair-meetup/
X-SOURCE:Meetup: WordPress Montclair
UID:event_311737693@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260412T031145Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260428T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260428T200000
SUMMARY:Compromise\, or Why I’m My Own Worst Coworker
DESCRIPTION:WordPress Montclair Meetup\nCompromise can be necessary to get
  things done but it’s just so hard sometimes\, especially when the stake
 s are high. I’ll talk about the strategies I use to decide what concessi
 ons to make and what to hold firm on. Also about realising that sometimes 
 compromise is unnecessary because it’s just me needing to get out of my 
 own way and the tactics I use to do exactly that.\n\nMary J Jay (JJ) is a 
 software engineer who’s been working with WordPress for over 15 years. S
 he currently works as a contract staff engineer at Vox Media where the per
 son she needs to compromise with the most to deliver good software on time
  is herself.\n\n\\-\\-\\-\nIf you would like to speak at a future meetup\,
  please reach out to any of our organizers in a meetup.com message or on o
 ur Slack.\n\n**PARKING**:\nWe've been asked to not park in the United Way 
 lot behind the library as it could result in a parking ticket. Please find
  street parking or a parking deck.\n\n\\-\\-\\-\nJoin the **JerseyPress Sl
 ack** group to chat with others in our community and get help: [https://je
 rseypress.org/slack/](https://jerseypress.org/slack/)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/wordpress-montclair-meetup/events/311
 737693/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20251027T204521Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251027T204521Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
