CATEGORIES:Social
CATEGORIES:Large Scale
DESCRIPTION:April is Sexual Assault Awareness Month\, and together\, we ca
 n break the silence. The Montclair State University Police Department and
  the Office of Advocacy & Outreach are committed to fostering a campus wh
 ere survivors feel heard\, supported\, and empowered. It starts with beli
 eving. It starts with you. By offering a safe and affirming response to t
 hose who disclose gender-based and sexual violence\, we can create lastin
 g change. Let’s stand together to end the cycle of silence—because every 
 voice matters\, and every action counts.\nDenim Day is recognized interna
 tionally as a day of action and awareness\, encouraging people to wear de
 nim to challenge victim-blaming and educate others about sexual violence.
  This year\, Denim Day falls on Wednesday\, April 29\, 2026.\nThe Univers
 ity Police and Office of Advocacy & Outreach and the Office of Advocacy a
 nd Community Resilience\, in partnership with over 30 campus and local co
 mmunity organizations\, invites you to join us from 9 a.m. to 12 p.m. at 
 the Amphitheater for a powerful awareness event honoring survivors and in
 creasing awareness of available resources.\nDespite the gaps that still e
 xist in the criminal justice system\, in resources\, and in prevention ed
 ucation\, we will move forward together as a community. As part of this c
 ommitment\, we will walk one mile around campus in solidarity with surviv
 ors.\n\nHosted by: Advocacy and Outreach\n\nAdditional Information can be
  found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/11871313
DTEND:20260429T160000Z
DTSTAMP:20260412T030706Z
DTSTART:20260429T130000Z
LOCATION:Amphitheater
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Denim Day 2026: Mind the Gaps\, Move Forward
UID:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/11871313
URL:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/11871313
X-HOSTS:Advocacy and Outreach
