DESCRIPTION:\nGraduate Conducting Recital Night\n\n\n \nThis recital highl
 ights the artistry and individuality of emerging conductors Gary Blackman
 \, Tristan Hughes\, and Alec Hamilton\, each leading chamber groups in a 
 diverse program. The performance offers a compelling look at the craft of
  conducting\, showcasing their interpretive insight\, leadership\, and co
 llaborative musicianship through performances of Copland's Appalachian Sp
 ring\, Barber's Knoxville Summer of 1915 and his Adagio for Strings\, as 
 well as works by Mozart and Beethoven.\n\n\n \n\n\nHosted by: The College
  of the Arts\n\nAdditional Information can be found at: https://montclair
 .campuslabs.com/engage/event/12369178
